SIMPLE: fulminating
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fulminating
<hw>Ful"mi*na"ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Thundering; exploding in a peculiarly sudden or violent
manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hurling denunciations, menaces, or
censures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fulminating oil</b></col>, <cd>nitroglycerin.</cd> --
<col><b>Fulminating powder</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <cd>any
violently explosive powder, but especially one of the fulminates, as
mercuric fulminate.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fulmination</ent>⟦br⟧
